The Prague Stock Exchange is falling into the minus against the closing of the business.
After the steep waste in the morning, the Prague Stock Exchange was able to correct the losses.
The transactions with the shares of ČEZ reached almost half of the normal daily business.
The Prague Stock Exchange, at the beginning of the Tuesday business, was linked to the break-in from Monday, when it fell by a further six percentage points.
This time the reason for the break-in was on Wall Street.
In the Czech Republic, too, the market's response to the result of the vote of the American House of Representatives, which had refused to support a stabilisation plan for the financial sector there, is shown.
Case of shares in Asia
On Tuesday, the shares on the Asian stock exchanges experienced a dramatic case, although the indices were able to compensate for some of the losses during the day.
The Hang Seng Exchange index in Hong Kong lost almost four percentage points over the business day, but later it was able to make up for a part of the losses, thus reducing the decrease to about 2.5 percent.
The Hang Seng China Enterprises index, which observed the movement of Chinese shares on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, fell by 3.8 percent, and in Shanghai the markets were closed.
The shares on the Sydney Stock Exchange lost more than five percent, but then reduced the losses to 4.3 percent.
The stock exchange in Taiwan decreased by 3.6 percent according to the index there.
"The timing for the US rescue operation is uncertain and will influence the financial markets worldwide," said the head of the Hong Kong monetary authority Joseph Yam.
Hong Kong, even though it belongs to China, determines its own monetary policy, that is, independent of the Chinese Central Bank.
The interest rates in Hong Kong are at the same level as those in the United States.
According to the Australian Prime Minister, Kevin Rudd, the American legislators should return to the negotiating table as soon as possible and adopt the draft financial support.
Otherwise, there is a threat that other countries will also be affected by the break-in.
A bloodbath of American shares
On Monday, the American House of Representatives rejected the plan to support the financial system, for which up to $700 billion (almost 12 trillion Kč) should be spent.
The legislators thus ignored President George Bush's request to support the plan.
In Bush's view, the plan would regulate the fundamental causes of the financial crisis and thus help to stabilise the whole economy.
The American shares experienced a bloodbath on Monday, and the main stock indices recorded the biggest fall in more than 20 years.
The Dow Jones Index fell by almost seven percent, with a similar break-in last in 1987.
The index had already fallen before the vote, but there was little evidence that the draft would not get through in the House of Representatives, the index had a free case.
Congress makes concession: US government is allowed to pump $700 billion into the banks
The top representatives of the American Congress and the government of President George W. Bush have agreed on a wider form of agreement on financial assistance to the American financial system.
This will be put to the vote at the beginning of next week.
The US legislators achieved a breakthrough in discussions on the adoption of a rescue plan in the form of a financial contribution to the American financial system of $700 billion (about 12 trillion kroner).
However, this does not yet mean a victory.
The Congressmen have to negotiate some details of the agreement before they can publish the final version of the law and vote on it.
The Financial System Support Plan will be negotiated in the American Congress on Monday.
On Sunday, the Chairman of the Committee on Banking and Financial Services, Barney Frank, of the Reuters Agency, said this.
In the Senate, different figures suggest that the plan could probably be voted on at the earliest on Wednesday.
According to economists, a communication on the adoption of the plan should be the first major psychological factor in the recovery of the financial markets.
But then there is a "disillusionment" due to the complex mechanisms that could be used to help the markets in practice.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
"We have made significant progress.
We have clarified our different views on what a market stabilisation package should look like, "said to the Bloomberg agency, the democracy Nancy Pelosi.
According to her, there could be a final vote on Sunday.
Representatives of the legislators met with the American Minister of Finance Henry Paulson on Sunday to give the government fund its final form.
This provides for the purchase of unsaleable mortgage assets from financial companies that are putting financial firms in serious losses and are jeopardising the stability of the entire system.
"We are on the verge of a definitive agreement on a plan that will work and which will have to be effective on the market.
It is necessary to continue the health plan, but I think we are at the target, "says Paulson.
A signal for Asian business
The global financial crisis is also clearly reflected in the stock markets, which are falling sharply.
According to the democratic senator of Nevada, Harry Reid, the legislators have tried to reach a final agreement in Congress before Sunday.
This is to reassure the investors of their business in the Asian financial markets, which are in the first time zone, where a decision by the Congress could affect the business on Monday.
However, it is not yet quite clear when both chambers of the American Congress will vote on the law, and there is also a lack of clarity as to whether the negotiations at the last minute could not still be a problem.
The legislators hope that it will be adopted in the next few days.
But the law will still experience some changes.
The total amount to be allocated to the system will be divided into two parts.
The initial $350 billion will be made available as soon as possible, as President George Bush requested.
But Congress can block the distribution of the remaining money if it has the impression that the program does not fulfil its function, with a further 100 billion dollars and later the final 350 billion dollars.
Bush appreciates progress in negotiations positive
The President has a right of veto in this decision, but the Congress can overvote his veto.
However, despite these changes, the basic idea of the programme has remained, based on the acquisition of finance for the purchase of bad mortgage securities, the value of which has fallen, because hundreds of thousands of Americans are no longer able to repay their mortgages.
"We have worked out everything.
The House of Representatives should be able to vote on the law on Sunday, and the Senate on Monday, "said Republican Senator Judd Gregg.
The American President Bush was also pleased with the progress made.
His spokesman Tony Fratto said that Bush was satisfied with the progress of Saturday and "appreciate the two-way effort to stabilise our financial markets and protect our economy."
Restriction of golden parachutes
The Chairman of the Banking Committee of the Senate Christopher Dodd, the leading negotiator, said that the legislators had agreed on a responsibility for the money programme, the protection of taxpayers from losses, the conclusion of benefits and a timetable for financing the plan.
The new law is also intended to limit the so-called golden parachutes for directors of companies involved in the programme and to set up a committee to supervise the Fund.
The Ministry of Finance will be responsible for this.
"We have worked very hard on it and have made great progress towards an agreement that works and is important for the market and for all Americans," said Paulson.
The plan also expects help for home owners who have problems with the repayment of their mortgage.
The government should negotiate new rates on mortgages it buys, with the aim of reducing the monthly costs for the debtors and allowing them to keep their homes.
Marek: Psychological assistance
The proposed plan is a good idea, according to the main economist of Patria Finance David Marek, but implementation will be very difficult.
"And that is because you do not know what mechanism and at what price the problem assets are bought up.
This will be crucial for how the financial sector and the government share the losses, "Marek said this week to the iHNed.cz. server.
In Marek's view, whether the plan is being adopted now or at the beginning of next week is not crucial.
"It is much more important that the Congressmen agree to support the plan and that they adopt it as soon as possible.
The psychological importance of the agreement on adoption is the most important thing at this moment, "Marek said.
