Actress Heather Locklear was arrested for driving under the effect of an unknown drug.
The actress Heather Locklear, known for the role of Amanda from the series "Melrose Place," was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara, California for driving under the influence of an unknown drug.
A witness had observed how she tried to get out of her parking lot in Montecito in a rather strange way, the spokesperson of the California traffic police reported to the magazine 'People'.
The witness told in detail that Locklear 'pressed through the gas pedal after 16: 30 and made a lot of noise by trying to move her car back or forward out of the parking lot, and as she drove backwards, she grabbed her sunglasses a few times.'
A little later, the witness, who had probably not known the actress at the beginning, saw that Locklear stopped on a nearby road and got out of the car.
The witness was the person who notified the emergency service because she 'had to live for Lockears'.
When the police strike came, they found the actress sitting in her car, standing across the street, blocking traffic.
'She seemed to be disoriented ', so they took the police to a special drug and alcohol center to take a test.
According to a police spokesman, the actress showed herself cooperative, excessive alcohol consumption was excluded from the first moment. 'Following the first observations of the officials, we believe that Locklear was under the influence of an unknown drug,' said the speaker.
Locklear was arrested under the suspicion of driving under the influence of an indefinite substance that could not be determined and brought to a local detention centre at 7: 00.
Two months ago, after treatment, Locklaer was released from the clinic in Arizona, where she was treated against anxiety and depression.
