The drivers who can become redue because of the alcohol level will have to install the 'Alcolock'.
The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for the alcohol level, installed in his car this system, which forbids him to start the car in the drunken state. If he is alcoholic, the car does not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the General Prosecutor's Office. According to it, it is a pilot project that will last for a year.
The purpose is to resocialize the driver, which is why he gets a course for the reeducation of traffic behaviour.
In addition to the General Prosecutor's Office, according to experience, the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for Safety of Automobiles will also participate.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of the drivers who were reported more than once for driving under the influence of alcohol were back in control.
The 'alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the air and prevents the start of the car when the driver has taken the alcohol test; or if an alcohol concentration is found which is higher than allowed.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the costs are borne by the person who imposed the penalty.
In this context, a study carried out in the US in 2007 has shown that cars equipped with these devices will prevent up to 65% of the standard infringements in the first year after its introduction.
In Spain, it is expected that 115 lives could be saved every year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to take action before it becomes a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate its implementation, a legal reform can be implemented by the ordinary means, and yet a reform of the basic law is required, which is necessary for the prosecution process.
The equipment is still available on the Spanish markets, in no business, even though it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and public transport vehicles.
Tomorrow, the House of Deputies will vote because of the initiative of the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party, which proposes to install this system in school buses, which has already been done in France.
