In a democracy, even slander have the right to speak.
What Barrick Gold does not understand - or does not want to understand - is that the public, who supports the authors and editors of Noir Canada, does so mainly because it rejects the brutal attitude of the gold mine.
This public is ready to listen to and judge Barrick, but on the basis of a civilized exchange of arguments, and not in a framework that many consider to be a knebel suit (in the course of the 'public debate', Barrick Gold has just made a request to the authors of Noir Canada, in which she asks them not to use this term...).
